  "prompt": "Why won't IFTTT link to my tumblr account?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why IFTTT might not be linking to your Tumblr account. Here's a breakdown of common culprits and how to troubleshoot them:\n\n**1. Incorrect Login Credentials:**\n\n*   **Username/Password:** Double-check that you're entering the correct Tumblr username/email and password. A simple typo can prevent the connection.\n*   **Tumblr Email vs. Username:** Try logging in with *both* your Tumblr email address and your Tumblr username. Sometimes IFTTT gets confused about which is used for authentication.\n\n**2. Tumblr Permission Issues:**\n\n*   **Authorization/Revoked Access:** You might have previously linked Tumblr to IFTTT, but then revoked access in your Tumblr account settings. To fix this:\n    1.  Go to your Tumblr settings (usually accessible by clicking your profile avatar in the top right, then \"Settings\").\n    2.  Look for a section related to \"Apps\" or \"Third-Party Applications.\"\n    3.  Find IFTTT in the list and make sure it's authorized. If not, revoke the access if it is there and try to link the accounts through IFTTT again.\n\n**3. IFTTT Service Outages or Bugs:**\n\n*   **IFTTT Status Page:** Check the IFTTT status page (status.ifttt.com) to see if there are any known issues or outages affecting the Tumblr service.  If there is an issue, all you can do is wait for them to resolve it.\n*   **IFTTT App Bugs:** Occasionally, there can be bugs in the IFTTT app itself. Try the following:\n    *   **Update the IFTTT App:** Make sure you're running the latest version of the IFTTT app on your phone or tablet.\n    *   **Restart IFTTT App:** Close the app completely and reopen it.\n    *   **Clear IFTTT App Cache:** (Android only) Go to your phone's settings, find the IFTTT app, and clear its cache.\n    *   **Reinstall IFTTT App:** As a last resort, try uninstalling and reinstalling the IFTTT app.\n\n**4. Browser-Related Problems:**\n\n*   **Cookies/Cache:** If you're linking through a web browser, clear your browser's cookies and cache.  This can sometimes resolve authentication issues.\n*   **Browser Extensions:** Some browser extensions can interfere with IFTTT's ability to connect to other services. Try disabling your extensions temporarily and see if that fixes the problem.\n*   **Different Browser:** Try linking Tumblr through a different web browser (e.g., if you're using Chrome, try Firefox or Safari).\n\n**5. Tumblr API Issues:**\n\n*   **Tumblr API Outage:**  Very rarely, the Tumblr API itself might be experiencing issues.  This is something IFTTT can't control, and you'll have to wait for Tumblr to resolve the problem.  Look for announcements on the Tumblr Engineering Blog or on Twitter (@tumblr).\n\n**6. Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) on Tumblr:**\n\n*   **App Password:** If you have Two-Factor Authentication enabled on your Tumblr account, you might need to create an app password specifically for IFTTT. Tumblr's 2FA may prevent standard login attempts from third-party apps. Check your Tumblr settings for instructions on how to generate an app password.  Use this app password instead of your regular Tumblr password when linking to IFTTT.\n\n**7. Account Restrictions:**\n\n* **Banned or Suspended Account:** If your Tumblr account has been banned or suspended, it will not be linkable.\n* **Account is Private:** While IFTTT should be able to access even private Tumblr accounts *after* being granted permission, it's possible there's a bug in how it handles initial connection.  Temporarily making your Tumblr account public, linking to IFTTT, and then making it private again *might* help. (But be cautious about changing privacy settings.)\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps (in order):**\n\n1.  **Double-check credentials:** Ensure your Tumblr username/email and password are correct. Try both the username and email.\n2.  **Check Tumblr Permissions:** Go to your Tumblr settings and make sure IFTTT is authorized. Revoke and re-authorize if necessary.\n3.  **Clear Browser Cache/Cookies (if linking via browser):**  Clear your browser's cache and cookies.\n4.  **Disable Browser Extensions (if linking via browser):**  Temporarily disable your browser extensions.\n5.  **Try a Different Browser (if linking via browser):** Use a different browser to link.\n6.  **Check IFTTT Status Page:** Verify if there are any known IFTTT or Tumblr service outages.\n7.  **Update/Restart/Reinstall IFTTT App:** Update, restart, or reinstall the IFTTT app.\n8.  **Clear IFTTT App Cache (Android):** Clear the IFTTT app's cache.\n9.  **Check for Tumblr API Issues:** See if Tumblr is experiencing API problems (though usually, IFTTT will show an error message in this case).\n10. **2FA App Password (if applicable):** Generate and use an app password for IFTTT if you have 2FA enabled on Tumblr.\n11. **Temporary Public Account (Cautiously):** If all else fails, temporarily make your Tumblr account public, link to IFTTT, and then make it private again.\n12. **Contact IFTTT Support:** If none of the above works, contact IFTTT support directly.  They may be able to provide more specific assistance.\n\nWhen contacting IFTTT support, provide as much detail as possible, including the specific error messages you are seeing, the steps you have already taken, and the type of device or browser you are using. Good luck!\n",
